<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1437,474,1183]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1086,1111]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Azevedo, 2000" authorityName="Santos &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2000" box="[679,1140,1086,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviramus">
<emphasis box="[679,840,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">A. breviramus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[850,1140,1086,1111]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refId="ref281771" refString="Santos, H. S. &amp; Azevedo, C. O. (2000) Sistematica das especies de Anisepyris Kieffer (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae) do Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 44, 129 - 165." type="journal article">Santos &amp; Azevedo, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
only by having the basal portion of the paramere narrow and sinuous with its apex not deflected to the inner region, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2000" box="[1278,1435,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviramus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1435,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">A. breviramus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the basal portion of the paramere wide and straight with its apex deflected to the inner region.
</paragraph>
